# Defensive whitelist : refuse everything in this directory by default,
# allow only files that are documented or known-encrypted.
#
# Rationale (see HIGH-4 in docs/audits/security-2026-05-03.md):
# the root .gitignore blocks `.env*` but NOT `.json`, `.txt`, `.yaml`
# (other than ones explicitly listed). A future `infra/secrets/openai-key.json`
# would slip through. This whitelist closes the gap.

*

# Documented + safe files
!.gitignore
!.sops.yaml
!README.md

# Templates (no real secrets)
!*.example

# Encrypted environment files. SOPS round-trips will keep these as text;
# anything under this name pattern that is NOT properly encrypted should
# fail the pre-commit hook (see CONTRIBUTING.md → Adding a secret).
!*.env
